This paper is likely to belong to the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with the problem of learning with unreliable label information, which is a common issue in machine learning. Additionally, the paper focuses on deep embedding learning, which is a subfield of machine learning that involves learning representations of data in a low-dimensional space. 

The paper also involves computer vision (cs.CV) as deep embedding learning is commonly used in image and video analysis. The use of triplet loss, which is a popular loss function for deep embedding learning, also suggests a focus on computer vision tasks. 

The paper may also belong to the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as deep learning is a subfield of AI and the paper deals with improving the effectiveness of unsupervised and weakly supervised learning, which are common approaches in AI. 

The category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also a possibility as the paper may involve natural language processing tasks, which often involve deep embedding learning. 

Finally, the category of cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possibility as deep embedding learning is commonly used in multimedia analysis tasks such as image and video retrieval.
